par1.stringValue: A Sollars Home™ is “manufactured at your site”.  We spend more time up front on blueprints and assembly drawings and this allows us to complete projects faster and at a higher level of quality.  Because we use the same “manufacturing flow” for all projects, we are able to complete a large percentage of a Sollars Home™ in house, thereby avoiding the markup charged by subcontractors to a traditional general contractor.  We can then pass these savings on to you!

par3.stringValue: A Sollars Home™ built from concrete using Multi-Flex Forming Technology fundamentally requires fewer steps than a wooden home and several of the remaining steps are simplified.  We simulate the construction process, which enables us to prefabricate many of the non-structural system pieces and incorporate them into the forming process, which slashes time when compared to having every piece of the home custom made on site.

par5.stringValue: A Sollars Home™ delivers the kind of energy savings you would expect from an advanced technology. The thermal mass of the concrete exoskeleton combined with the increased insulation that is standard in a Sollars Home™ serves to stabilize the interior temperature on even the hottest days. This unique combination works equally well in the winter and results in year-round energy efficiency that you can see in your utility bills.

par6.stringValue: With Multi-Flex Forming Technology, we are able to build a Sollars Home™ from almost any design that can be drawn on a piece of paper.  A basement is an option for all Sollars Home™ and we can easily handle varying roof pitches, wall heights, wall widths, and window/door sizes and locations.  Special design items like 45 degree angles, fireplaces, bay windows, elevators, and decks do not pose a problem either.  Even complex roof configurations and round sections can be constructed!  If you can envision it, we can build it!

par8.stringValue: Safer, quieter, more comfortable, more tranquil. Sustainability and permanence into everything we do. A Sollars Home™ will look good for a very long time

par9.stringValue: We can handle complex, multi-faceted projects for even the most discerning of clients while offering high value at competitive prices.

par10.stringValue: Affordable construction costs and rapid completion means your investment puts more money in your wallet sooner.

par11.stringValue: “Bulletproof” storage for your precious classics. Ask us about our “ultra-secure” storage options.

par12.stringValue: Tranquil sanctuaries that allow you to escape from life’s distractions so that you can produce at your full potential.

par13.stringValue: Open, airy spaces that let you indulge your wet and wild side. We can also design and build your pool and pool deck.

par15.stringValue: When I entered the construction industry after careers as a microprocessor architect and manufacturing engineer, I was shocked at the lack of technological innovation. Having established a successful construction and contracting business, I envisioned a new way of building centered around “manufacturing” a home from concrete at the site.

par16.stringValue: Using a more advanced construction technology, we cast an entire building, all at once, at the site, in a process that also incorporates the framing, plumbing, electrical, and heating/AC systems. By compressing what used to take 3 or 4 casting cycles into a single casting cycle that includes additional trades, we alter the fundamental economics of building such that it is now feasible, even preferable, to build with concrete instead of wood. We combine the flexibility of our technology with an innovative manufacturing-based approach to offer a new business model and buying experience for our clients. Over time, we will unveil new capabilities that are unique to a Sollars Home.

par17.stringValue: As an established company with an exciting new technology, it is our mission to redefine how building is done and to make the Sollars Home the dwelling of choice for human beings.

par18.stringValue: People won’t be forced to live in a wooden home any more!

par19.stringValue: We can design and build a Sollars Home™ for you directly, or we can work hand in hand with your team (architect, engineer/s, general contractor, etc) to build your project to the design that your team would provide.

par20.stringValue: We can work as the structural subcontractor to produce the building’s “shell”.  The rough electrical ↦ plumbing trades are included, but we can also do framing, roofing, stucco, insulation, & windows/exterior doors to get you to the equivalent of a “rough framing” inspection.

par21.stringValue: We can work with you in the role of the General Contractor to complete your custom designed project for your client.  We also offer a library of pre-designed models, that can be customized, to serve as outbuildings in your larger project.

par22.stringValue: We service the cities within about a 50 mile radius of our offices in San Jose, California.

par23.stringValue: The Sollars Home™ is a new product and company launched by its parent company, Sollars Construction, Inc., which has been doing custom concrete projects in the Silicon Valley for over 10 years. Sollars Home™ is a privately held company with its headquarters at 1701 Rogers Avenue, Unit 40, San Jose, CA.

par29.stringValue: Don Sollars holds his Bachelors of Science in Electrical Engineering from the University of Illinois. With a working knowledge of architecture, structures, and civil engineering, Don was able to create the Sollars Home™ (™). Don enjoys hiking and spending time with his German Shepherd, Storm

par30.stringValue: Native to the Bay Area, Clay has 40 years of experience as a Machinist, Welder, and Fabricator. In his spare time, he enjoys riding Harleys and watching blues bands.

par31.stringValue: Daughter of Don Sollars and Bay Area native, Erika has a Bachelors of Science in Marketing from Arizona State University. When she is not hard at work, Erika loves to play basketball and travel.

par32.stringValue: Born and raised in San Jose, California, Andrew holds his Bachelors of Science in Mechanical Engineering from San Jose State University. Andrew likes to spend his free time playing racquetball and golf.

par33.stringValue: Raymond was born and raised in Northern California and has a Bachelors of Science in Mechanical Engineering from San Jose State University. Raymond’s hobbies include badminton and traveling.

par34.stringValue: Sollars Home™ truly respects the unyielding power of Mother Nature. Therefore, we have engineered extremely safe buildings that are resistant against the forces of nature (earthquakes, fire, flood, wind, mold, termites, and more). Concrete is a material proven to stand the test of time and we are proud to be a company committed to improving the health of our planet through sustainable practices.

par35.stringValue: At Sollars Home™, it is our intention to be a “Carbon-Neutral Builder”. For every structure we build, we will offset the carbon Footprint by planting enough trees to eliminate the Carbon Dioxide produced by the project in a 30 year timeframe. After the CO2 output is balanced, the trees planted for each building will continue to absorb CO2 during the remainder of their lifespan such that we can do our small part to contribute to a healthier planet.

header2.stringValue: Our revolutionary technology allows us to cast our buildings from concrete--with floor, walls, and roof all poured at your site on the same day.

header9.stringValue: YOU'LL LOVE THE WAY YOU FEEL IN A SOLLARS HOME

header10.stringValue: At Sollars Home™, we are custom builders at heart. We can build a Sollars Home™ of practically any size, shape, or configuration you can envision. We also offer pre-designed standard buildings for specific uses that are terrific values.

list16.stringValue: "That we can build a Sollars Home™ into a hillside at a fraction of the cost of other builders"

list17.stringValue: "That a Sollars Home™ naturally acts as a retaining wall"

list18.stringValue: "That a Sollars Home™ creates a sound barrier that dramatically reduces noise from freeways, overpasses, etc."

list19.stringValue: "That we can tackle your ENTIRE backyard makeover including pool, pool house, retaining walls, landscape, and hardscape using concrete, pavers, and natural stone"
